Describe a time when you received money as a gift

I’m going to talk about a celebration that my parents organized for me, which is one of the most memorable events I’ve ever experienced.

Although it took place nearly two years ago, I can still remember it very clearly. At that time, I had just turned 18 and had completed my national university entrance exam, which is considered one of the most important milestones for students in Vietnam. Fortunately, I passed with flying colors, so my parents were absolutely delighted.

To celebrate this achievement, they decided to host a small gathering at our house with close friends and relatives. At the beginning, my parents briefly explained the purpose of the celebration. After that, everyone took turns congratulating me and giving me their best wishes, along with some thoughtful gifts.

Later on, we all sat down together to enjoy a meal and shared a few drinks in a warm and cheerful atmosphere. Before the event ended, we took plenty of photos to capture the moment.

Once everyone had left, I opened all the presents and realized that most of them, especially from my relatives, were in the form of money. Altogether, it added up to around 25 million Vietnamese dong, which is over 1,000 US dollars. It was actually the first time I had ever held such a large amount of money, so I was absolutely thrilled.

My parents told me I could spend it however I liked, and I eventually decided to buy myself a new phone, which I’m still using today.

Overall, it was an unforgettable experience, and I truly hope I’ll have the chance to celebrate another special milestone like that in the future.
